# Architecture rules

## Single source of truth

`src/stores/gameStore.ts` owns ALL game state. No component may hold a local copy of grid data, placed words, selection state, score, or game-over flags. Read reactively from the store; write only through store actions.

## Unidirectional data flow

```
wordLists.ts  →  gameStore  ←  useWordPlacement.ts
                    ↕
               useSelection.ts
                    ↓
         WordGrid → WordCell
         WordList
         GameControls → gameStore (via actions)
```

## Composable responsibilities

- `useWordPlacement.ts` — pure function, no Vue reactivity, no store access. Receives a grid and word pool, returns a mutated grid and `PlacedWord[]`.
- `useSelection.ts` — bridges DOM events (mouse + touch) to store state. Calls `store.validateSelection()` on drag end. No game logic here.

## Adding a word theme

Add an entry to `wordThemes` in `src/data/wordLists.ts` and add its key to the `Theme` union type. Nothing else needs to change.

## Adding a difficulty level

Add entries to `DIFFICULTY_SIZE` and `DIFFICULTY_WORDS` in `gameStore.ts`, and a `{ value, label }` entry to `difficulties` in `GameControls.vue`.
